Package dog.giraffe.image.transform

Interface Mask

  • public interface Mask
    Describes masks that can be applied to clustering algorithms to disregard data points.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      static Mask all()
      Creates a mask that allows all points to be clustered.
      static Mask and​(java.util.List<Mask> masks)
      Creates the intersection of all the masks.
      static Mask halfPlane​(double cx, double cy, double cc)
      Creates a new mask that enables point (xx,yy) when it is in the solution of cx*xx+cy*yy+cc >= 0.0
      static Mask halfPlane​(double x1, double y1, double x2, double y2)
      Creates a new mask the enables points which are on the left of the half-plane specified be the (x1,y1)->(x2,y2) vector.
      boolean visible​(double xx, double yy)
      Return whether the point (xx, yy) visible through this mask.

    • Method Detail

      • all

        static Mask all()
        Creates a mask that allows all points to be clustered.

      • and

        static Mask and​(java.util.List<Mask> masks)
        Creates the intersection of all the masks. Any point masked out by any mask will be masked out in the new mask too.
